Auginte - a tool to augment the meaning of complex and heterogeneous information
================================================================================

WARNING
-------

    This is only ALPHA version of the software.
    Some functionality is not supported, software can crash or corrupt opened data.
    Do not use with sensitive information! Always consider making backups.


Requirements
------------

 * Java 7+ (JRE 1.7 or higher): http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jre7-downloads-1880261.html


Running from Linux/Unix
-----------------------

    Execute ./bin/auginte


Running from Windows
--------------------

    Execute bin\auginte.bat


Running from other OS
---------------------

	java -cp "lib/*:$JAVA_HOME/jre/lib/jfxrt.jar" com.auginte.desktop.Auginte

	Where $JAVA_HOME is something like /usr/lib/jvm/java-7-oracle


Installing globally on Linux
----------------------------

    sudo make install PREFIX="/usr/local"
    auginte


Connect to other database
-------------------------

    Auginte is using OrientDB database to store data.
    To connect to your own database, execute program with parameters. For example:

        ./bin/auginte --dbConnection=remote --dbName=localhost/auginte --dbUser=root --dbPassword=secret


